Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows significantly elevated creatinine in both serum and blood, indicating impaired renal function. Urinalysis reveals marked proteinuria, glucosuria, ketonuria, low specific gravity, and abnormal urine appearance (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal), suggesting possible nephrotic syndrome or advanced diabetic nephropathy, though HbA1c is low. No evidence of urinary infection. Immediate nephrology evaluation is recommended for further assessment and management.
